author: Arata Yamamoto
title: Japanese state of emergency has some success but trains still packed
description: Prime Minister Shinzo Abe announced the measure for Tokyo, Osaka and other areas as the nationwide tally of coronavirus cases rose to more than 4,600, with 98 confirmed deaths.
content:
Japan's state of emergency imposed in parts of the country this week is having mixed results, with previously busy areas becoming deserted while some commuter trains are packed Wednesday morning.
